OL,6,FWhat is the risk of naming a child
OL,7,Fsuspect in a criminal investigation?
OL,9,FChildren over 10 have reached the
OL,10,Fcriminal age of responsibility in
OL,11,FEngland and Wales, meaning those aged
OL,12,Fbetween 10 and 17 can be arrested and
OL,13,Ftaken to court.
OL,15,FThe identity of defendants and
OL,16,Fwitnesses under the age of 18 who are
OL,17,Fsubject to criminal proceedings in
OL,18,Fyouth courts is protected by automatic
OL,19,Freporting restrictions.
