OL,6,FPress regulator IPSO advises editors
OL,7,Fto "generally avoid naming children
OL,8,Funder the age of 18 after arrest for a
OL,9,Fcriminal offence but before they
OL,10,Fappear in a youth court unless they
OL,11,Fcan show that the individual's name is
OL,12,Falready in the public domain, or that
OL,13,Fthe individual or their guardian has
OL,14,Fgiven their consent".
OL,16,FIf restrictions are imposed, or
OL,17,Fautomatic restrictions apply, child
OL,18,Fdefendants remain anonymous throughout
OL,19,Flegal proceedings and the rulings can
OL,20,Fbe challenged ` usually by reporters `
OL,21,Fafter the court case has ended.
